              When you eat cannabis, your liver converts THC into 11-hydroxy-THC, which is more potent and crosses the blood-brain barrier more effectively. This metabolite produces stronger, more psychoactive effects compared to the delta-9-THC that reaches your brain when smoking.
            </div>
